10/11/2006
BELGRADE, Montenegro -- Greek Defence Minister Evangelos Meimarakis and his Serbian counterpart, Zoran Stankovic, sealed a defence agreement Thursday (November 9th) in Belgrade.
The accord envisages intensifying military training and co-operation between training centre for peace operations in Belgrade and Kilkis, Greece.
Meanwhile, Slovak Foreign Minister Jan Kubis kicked off an official visit to Athens Thursday (November 9th) at the invitation of his Greek counterpart, Dora Bakoyannis.
The two focused on economic relations and a possible increase of Greek investments in Slovakia, as well as on the possibility of boosting tourism co-operation.
(ANA-MPA - 09/11/06)
